{c-- BRIEFING NOTES FOR EXERCISE MISSIONS --


	MISSION ........... {tSINGLE LANDING}} (exercise)
	AIRCRAFT .......... as selected
	ARMAMENT .......... standard (practice)
	POSITION .......... 10nm south of Wattisham
	IAS ............... 400kts
	HEADING ........... 010°
	HEIGHT ............ 3000ft
	WEATHER ........... Blue
	PARENT AIRFIELD ... Wattisham
	TASK .............. land at Wattisham,runway 05.
	ALLOCATED TIME .... 10 minutes.


This is the first exercise mission you need to complete. It gives you access
to others and they in turn will give you access to more until all missions
in this list have been successfully completed and you have 'qualified'.
To make an exercise mission count for your qualification it must be completed
in time and without any errors at all. It is quite frustrating to return from
a successful mission and collect a >TAIL HIT GROUND< or >BRAKES OVERHEATED<
error on landing.
A mission is logged as completed after landing and stopping on the required
runway - a checkmark in the exercise list indicates success.
Special rules apply during the qualification stage: You only have access to
the cockpit interior, the on-board radar and the map. All external view modes
and access to the surveillance radar, approach radar and aircraft movements
screen is blocked.
The pause function ({hDEL}) is also blocked and you cannot stop and continue
your flight in the usual fashion. If the program is halted with {hHELP} you
must start again with >RESET< or >RUN<. All these restrictions are lifted
after you have completed a mission or after you have made an error. Always
save your qualification after landing, a requester will remind you to do so
within ten seconds of coming to a halt after landing.


