{c-- BRIEFING NOTES FOR EXERCISE MISSIONS --


	MISSION ........... {tCAP (DAY)}} (exercise)
	AIRCRAFT .......... Lightning,F-104
	ARMAMENT .......... standard (practice/live)
	POSITION .......... on runway 06,Leeuwarden
	IAS ............... -
	HEADING ........... -
	HEIGHT ............ -
	WEATHER ........... Blue
	PARENT AIRFIELD ... Leeuwarden
	TASK .............. CAP exercise (land at Leeuwarden,runway 06)
	ALLOCATED TIME .... 30 minutes (30 minutes)
	REMARKS ........... one 'kill' required for qualification


Take off as pair and fly a combat air patrol to the north of the airfield.
Two aircraft are approaching from the north, you are required to score at
least one 'kill' and land back at Leeuwarden. This exercise is flown with
dummy (practice) missiles and guns as the 'DACT' missions before.
At this stage, however, you are allowed to select ARMAMENT: >>LIVE<< to use
real missiles. If you choose to do this, the incoming targets will also be
armed with live missiles.
Select channel 'air-to-air' after take-off and as soon as your wingman
reports target contact you hit 'engage'.


