{c-- BRIEFING NOTES FOR EXERCISE MISSIONS --


	MISSION ........... {tMPC (HEAD-ON)}} (exercise)
	AIRCRAFT .......... Lightning F.6 or F.3
	ARMAMENT .......... two Red Top missiles (live)
	POSITION .......... 20nm north-west of Valley
	IAS ............... 615kts (1.60M)
	HEADING ........... 180°
	HEIGHT ............ 32,000ft
	WEATHER ........... Blue
	PARENT AIRFIELD ... Valley
	TASK .............. destroy target (land at Valley,runway 14).
	ALLOCATED TIME .... 3 minutes (30 minutes).


Only Lightning F.6 and F.3 carry Red Top missiles for head-on attacks.
This mission is not required for qualification on F-104.
Rate of closure during this attack is 1700kts or 2900ft per second, you must
be extremely fast to acquire the target and make minor course corrections.
Expect target contact after 90 seconds. It is probably safer to launch your
missiles as a pair; press {hK} or make this selection with the mouse by
clicking the 'Pairs Firing Selector'. There is not sufficient time to turn
through 180dgr and launch the second missile in pursuit, so you may as well
use both missiles in one go.
Launch missiles as soon as you pass the outer range bracket, rate of closure
during this attack is so high that any second counts.


